== Etymology ==
Old English ''þreo'', from Germanic ''*þrijiz'', from PIE ''*treyes''. Cognate to German ''drei'', French ''trois'', Greek ''τρεις'', Russian ''три''.

== Number ==
# [[One]] plus [[two]]. Represented in Roman numerals as III and in Arabic numerals as 3. The typical number of parts in most [[monocot]] [[flower]]. Ordinal: [[third]].

